<TITLE> Tarique bail extended, Babar bail upheld </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 23 (bdnews24.com) - The Appellate Division on Thursday extended the interim bail of Tarique Rahman, elder son of former prime minister Khaleda Zia, in a bribery case relating to the murder of a Basundhara Group director. The Appellate Division also upheld six-months bail for former state minister Lutfozzaman Babar in an arms case, in which he has been sentenced to 17 years. The HC granted him interim bail in the case on Oct 16. A full Appellate Division bench, led by chief justice MM Ruhul Amin, extended the duration of Tarique's bail by three months, in the bribery case which accuses him of taking money to suppress the murder of Humayun Kabir Sabbir. Tarique secured bail in the case on Aug 27. The High Court on Thursday granted interim bail to former BNP law minister Moudud Ahmed and former lawmaker Mosaddek Ali Falu. The HC bench of justices Mohammad Anwarul Haque and Farah Mahbub granted the three-month bail to Moudud in a case charging him with amassing illegal wealth. Moudud's lawyer Barrister Rafique-ul Huq sought bail from the court on medical grounds. He also pointed out that that proceedings of the case had been stayed by the Supreme Court. Another HC bench comprising justices Syed Mohammad Dastagir Hossain and Farid Ahmed granted three-month bail to former lawmaker Mosaddek Ali Falu in a case on charge of misappropriating relief materials. Barrister Rafique-ul Huq also stood for Falu in the court. bdnews24
